P(n,k)
 P(n,k,even) = 1-P(n,k)
 P(n,k) = P(n,n+1-k) 
 P(n,k) =0\ \text{ if }\ k\le 0\ \text{ or }\ k>n
 P(1,1) = 1
 \begin{align*} P(n,k ) &=\frac12\cdot (1- P(n-1,k))+\frac12\cdot (1-P(n-1,k-1))  \\ &=1-\frac12\cdot\left(P(n-1,k)+P(n-1,k-1)\right) \end{align*}
P(2,1) = 1/2
P(3,1)=1-1/2\cdot(P(2,1)+P(2,0))=3/4
P(3,2)=1-1/2\cdot(P(2,2)+P(2,1)) = 1/2
P(4,1)=1-1/2\cdot3/4 = 5/8
P(4,2)=1-1/2\cdot(1/2+3/4)=3/8
